sts but is never used by the controller. According to the exec plan, registratio
n and login are merged into `POST /auth/login`, so this file should be removed.\
n\n3. **API Contract incomplete**: `docs/api-contracts/auth.yaml` is missing the
`POST /api/v1/auth/logout` endpoint even though it's implemented in the controll
er.\n\n4. **Mobile unit tests missing**: There are no unit tests for the Flutter
AuthBloc or AuthInterceptor. The only tests are generated OpenAPI model tests.\n
\n5. **`shared-types` Dart package invalid**: `packages/shared-types` has a `pub
spec.yaml` but no `lib/` directory, making it an invalid Dart package dependency
. However, it may not be actively imported in the mobile code I've seen.\n\n6. *
*BDD test dependency on build artifacts**: `tests/bdd/step-definitions/bdd-setup
.js` imports from `../../../apps/api/dist/`, meaning `make test-bdd` will fail u
nless `npm run build` is executed first. The Makefile doesn't ensure this.\n\n7.
**Inconsistent `is_new_user` semantics in `getMe`**: `AuthService.getMe()` retur
ns `is_new_user` based on profile completeness (`!user.profile || !user.profile.
isComplete`), but `login()` returns it based on whether the user was just create
d. This is confusing naming - `getMe` should probably return `profile_complete` 
only, not `is_new_user`. But the BLoC handles it with `isNewUser || me.isNewUser
